To evaluate the value of local balancing (LB) this contribution considers costs for conventional grid reinforcement (reference scenario). Only reinforcement that can be avoided by local balancing gain value. Gained value will be allocate as a compensation on the total number (n) of electrolysis (x). The allocation was calculated based on energy and power of the PEM during the time-period (p). This approach was general described in Eq. (1).1CLB(x,n)=CLB,annual·0.5·EH2xEH2,totn+0.5·P¯H2xP¯H2,totn\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
